                    <TD valign="top" ><H2 align="left">Your Picture Post
                        </H2>
                      <P>It is a great feeling to get a new Picture Post in the ground!  </P>
                      <P>The value of any post is in the commitment of people to take pictures on a regular basis and for many years. It is not always easy to keep up the initial excitement, but we hope that the Picture Post network will offer incentives and provide participants with valuable information that will be rewarding as the network grows and matures.</P>
                        <P>A Picture Post owner is responsible for:</P>
                        <UL>
                          <LI>setting up and adding your post to the website
                          <LI>monitoring submissions and making sure that pictures meet your requirements                          
                          <LI>deleting inappropriate material or poor quality pictures - anyone can help by flagging a picture as inappropriate 
                          <LI>choosing the reference set of photographs - you can change the reference set whenever you like
                          <LI>photographer's notes and comments on the reference set of pictures - these are helpful for others to learn what you are monitoring and why it is important. 
                          <LI>Your notes and comments are best if they include names or species of plants of interest and other items you want people to watch for.
                      </UL>
                        <P>To help you, we have put in place some features on &quot;My Page&quot;. Once you are logged in &quot;My Page&quot; appears in the navigation bar at the top of the page.</P>
<P>Here, you can keep track of the post(s) you own. To access and manage your post, click on the post name that appears in the list on this page.                      </P>
<P>As the post owner, you will receive an email anytime that pictures are uploaded to your post. We also suggest that you designate an alternate responsible person (co-owner) who can take responsibility on your behalf.</P>
                      <P>Ownership can be transferred. To change owners, please <A HREF="/contact.jsp">contact us</A>.</P></TD>
